European Central Bank council member
 Erkki Liikanen  said the European Union should establish a common
supervisory body for systemically important, cross-border banks,
 WirtschaftsWoche  reported, citing an interview.  A common resolution process and a deposit guarantee system
should also be created, the magazine reported, citing Liikanen.  To contact the reporter on this story:
